# Leo Planner — Make it an App (Simple Plan)

**App name:** **Leo Planner**
**Icon:** the 🦁 lion-face **emoji** (Noto/Android style) on the brand teal square (`public/leo-icon.svg` + generated PNGs) — wired everywhere.
**Order (cheapest first):** **PWA ($0) → install on Fire tablet → (optional, later) APK / Play Store → (optional, much later) iOS.**

Legend:
- 🤖 = I (the AI) do it in the code/repo
- 🧑 = You do it (needs a person, an account, a device, or a payment)
- 💲 = Costs money

---

## The plan in one line
We are **NOT** building a native app or paying anyone right now. Leo Planner is already a **PWA** (installable web app). We polish it, you install it on the **Fire tablet** from the browser, and that's a real $0 "app". Stores come later only if you want them.

---

## Your questions answered

**Q: $0 approach = PWA?** ✅ Yes. PWA ("Add to Home Screen" / "Install app") costs nothing, needs no store account, and runs full-screen with the lion icon on Fire tablet, Android, iPhone, and desktop.

**Q: Will it still use Supabase, or local storage on the device?** **Both — and PWA changes nothing here.**
- **Supabase** stays the cloud backend when you're **signed in** (sync across devices, groups/sharing, account data).
- **localStorage on the device** is still used for the offline app shell and cached/local data.
- The **Vault stays client-side encrypted** (AES-256) either way.
- **Internet:** sign-in and cloud sync need internet. Already-loaded screens and locally cached data still open offline; changes sync when you're back online.
- So: same architecture as today, just launched from a home-screen icon instead of a browser tab.

**Q: App name?** Set to **Leo Planner** (manifest, title, meta — already done).

**Q: Lion icon?** The lion face (`leo-icon.svg`) is already the PWA/app icon and favicon. One small gap remains (PNG sizes) — see A1.

---

## Good news — most of this is already done ✅
- `public/manifest.json` named **"Leo Planner"** with the lion icon and app shortcuts. ✅
- Service worker registered (`public/service-worker.js`) for offline + install. ✅
- App is hosted on **HTTPS** (`leo-planner.vercel.app`) — required for PWA install. ✅
- Favicon now points to the lion icon. ✅ (🤖 fixed)
- **Lion PNG icons generated** (192, 512, maskable 192/512, apple-touch 180, 144 tile) and wired into `manifest.json` + `index.html`. ✅ (🤖 done — regenerate anytime with `node scripts/generate-icons.mjs`)

**Remaining gaps:** none for install. Optional later: a PNG **splash** and store screenshots (only needed for an APK/store listing).

