## PHASE A — PWA first ($0) ← do this now

### A1. Polish the PWA
- ✅ 🤖 🦁 emoji icon (Noto lion on teal) — SVG + PNGs (192/512/maskable/apple-touch/tile) generated and wired into `manifest.json` + `index.html`. Regenerate with `node scripts/generate-icons.mjs`.
- ✅ 🤖 Favicon points to the lion icon; manifest validates ("Leo Planner", 6 icons).
- 🧑 (After deploy) verify "installable" on the tablet/desktop — browser DevTools → Application → Manifest should show no errors and an Install option.
- 🤖 (Optional) PNG splash screen in the Leo palette.

### A2. Publish the latest build
- 🧑 Push to git (you do this manually). Vercel auto-deploys `leo-planner.vercel.app`.
- 🤖 I prep the build/changes; you push.

### A3. Install on the Fire tablet (see detailed Fire steps below)
- 🧑 Follow the Fire tablet steps and tell me what happens.

### A4. Test & fix
- 🧑 Use it on the Fire tablet; report anything broken (layout, offline, login). 🤖 I fix, you re-test.

✅ **Phase A done = a free, installed Leo Planner on your Fire tablet.**

