## Fire tablet — how to install (Fire OS is Android-based)

Pick the easiest route that works for you. All are **$0**.

### Route 1 — Silk browser, Add to Home Screen (simplest)
- 🧑 Open the **Silk** browser on the Fire tablet.
- 🧑 Go to **`leo-planner.vercel.app`** and sign in once.
- 🧑 Tap the **menu (⋮)** → **"Add to Home Screen"** (wording may vary).
- 🧑 Confirm. The lion icon appears on the home screen; tapping it opens Leo Planner.
- ⚠️ Note: Silk's PWA support is basic — it may open more like a browser shortcut than a full standalone app. If that bugs you, use Route 2.

### Route 2 — Chrome on Fire (better full-screen PWA)
- 🧑 Allow installing apps: **Settings → Security & Privacy → Apps from Unknown Sources** (enable for the file app/browser).
- 🧑 Download the **Chrome** APK from a reputable source (e.g. APKMirror) and install it. (Chrome isn't in the Amazon Appstore.)
- 🧑 Open `leo-planner.vercel.app` in Chrome → menu → **"Install app"** → it runs standalone with the lion icon.
- 🤖 I can give you the exact tap-by-tap if you choose this route.

### Route 3 — Real installable APK (optional, still $0, no store)
- 🤖 Package the PWA into an **APK** using **PWABuilder** (uses our HTTPS site + manifest — no rewrite).
- 🧑 Copy the APK to the Fire tablet and install it (Unknown Sources on).
- Result: a true app icon + standalone window, **without** any store or fee.
- This is also the bridge to the Play Store later (same package).

> Recommended: start with **Route 1** (30 seconds). If you want it to feel like a "real app," do **Route 2** or **Route 3**.

---

## PHASE B — APK / Google Play (optional, later)
Only if you want a store listing instead of sideloading.
- 🤖 Build the APK/AAB from the PWA (PWABuilder/Bubblewrap) — reuses the same lion icon + manifest.
- 💲 🧑 **Google Play Developer account — $25 one-time.**
- 🧑 Create the signing key and keep it safe (🤖 gives exact command).
- 🧑 Upload build + fill listing in Play Console (🤖 drafts the text; you add screenshots).
- 🧑 Submit for review.

## PHASE C — iOS App Store (optional, much later)
- 💲 🧑 **Apple Developer Program — $99/year.**
- 💲 🧑 **A Mac** (own or ~$20–60/mo cloud rental) — required for iOS builds.
- 🤖 Generate the iOS wrapper (Capacitor) from the same source; draft the listing.
- 🧑 Build/sign/upload in Xcode + App Store Connect; submit for review.

---

## Money checklist
- [x] **PWA install (Fire tablet, phone, desktop)** — **$0**
- [x] **Sideloaded APK (Route 3)** — **$0**
- [ ] 💲 Google Play — **$25 once** (only for a Play Store listing)
- [ ] 💲 Apple Developer — **$99/year** (only for the iOS App Store)
- [ ] 💲 Mac access — only for iOS

> No monthly fees for the PWA, Capacitor, or build tools. The only recurring cost is Apple's $99/year, and only if you choose the iOS App Store.

---

## Split of work
- 🤖 **I do:** icon PNGs, manifest/HTML polish, installability checks, optional APK packaging, all store text, bug fixes.
- 🧑 **You do:** push to git (auto-deploys), install on the Fire tablet, test/report, and — only if you go to stores — pay the fees, create the signing key, take screenshots, and click "Submit."
